sequenceDiagram
    participant DSP as DSP API Server
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant WFC as workflow-controller<br/>Watch/Informer
    participant Pod as Workflow Pod<br/>(argoexec sidecar)
    participant S3 as S3/MinIO<br/>443/TCP or 9000/TCP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/TCP or 3306/TCP

    Note over DSP,DB: Flow 1: Workflow Execution

    DSP->>K8s: 1. Create Workflow CR<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8s-->>WFC: 2. Watch event (Workflow created)<br/>Informer/TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    WFC->>K8s: 3. Create Pod for workflow step<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8s-->>Pod: Pod scheduled and started<br/>(argoexec injected as emissary)

    Pod->>Pod: Execute step container

    Pod->>S3: 5. Upload artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Access Key/Secret
    S3-->>Pod: Artifact stored

    Pod->>K8s: 4. Patch WorkflowTaskResult<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

    WFC->>K8s: Update Workflow status<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    WFC->>DB: 6. Archive workflow<br/>TCP/5432 or 3306<br/>TLS (configurable)<br/>Auth: Username/Password

    Note over DSP,DB: Flow 2: CronWorkflow Scheduling

    WFC->>WFC: Cron ticker fires
    WFC->>K8s: 1. Create Workflow from CronWorkflow<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    WFC->>K8s: 2. Update CronWorkflow status<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
